b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av116.htm)  [Next](av118.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 9. Charm to secure the love of a woman.\n\n1\\. Hanker thou after my body, my feet, hanker after my eyes, my thighs! The\neyes of thee, as thou lustest after me, and thy hair shall be parched with\nlove?  \n2\\. I make thee cling to my arm, cling to my heart, so that thou shalt be in\nmy power, shalt come up to my wish!  \n3\\. The cows, the mothers of the ghee, who lick their young, in whose heart\nlove is planted, shall make yonder woman bestow love upon me!\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VI, 102. Charm to secure the love of a woman](av118.htm)\n\n'